"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":290,"output":405,"cacheRead":44416,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45111,"cost":{"input":0.0007250000000000001,"output":0.0060750000000000005,"cacheRead":0.011104,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.017904}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775233845608,"responseId":"resp_02913ec245aa55fb0169cfeb35dd388191a71bb610809cafd6"}}
{"type":"message","id":"6510483b","parentId":"99743b3d","timestamp":"2026-04-03T16:30:58.685Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_W6lpG0BiShD2z0sUMon059V5|fc_02913ec245aa55fb0169cfeb4281b48191b906d7b43b5b85e7","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Real Run Validation — 2026-04-03\n\n## Goal\nValidate the next execution tranche for Block 2 with a real OpenClaw path narrower than the full sector: bootstrap B2/S3 correctly, run at least one real S3 operator agent, validate its output structurally, compile sector artifacts, and observe what still blocks Paperclip/Perseus activation of `b2_director -> S3`.\n\n## What was changed\n\n### 1. `helpers/build_s3_bootstrap_from_b2.py`\nUpgraded the generated `s3_source_package.json` so it now mirrors the shape documented in `S3/inputs.md` much more closely:\n- reads `screenplay_analysis.json`\n- optionally reads `01_script_fetched.json`\n- writes `video_context`\n- writes `script_overview`\n- writes normalized `scenes[]`\n- preserves `entity_focus` and upstream input references\n\n### 2. `S3/helpers/build_operator_dispatches.py`\nAdded narrow-run support:\n- can now emit dispatches for all operators\n- or for one selected operator only\n- writes an activation plan that explicitly marks the inactive operators\n\n### 3. `helpers/real_run_b2_s3_one_operator.py`\nAdded a mechanical validation runner that:\n- creates an isolated run root\n- bootstraps B2 in `s3_only`\n- builds canonical S3 bootstrap + source package\n- generates dispatch for one selected operator\n- invokes the real OpenClaw operator agent via `openclaw agent --agent ...`\n- validates operator output against schema\n- compiles `compiled_entities.json`\n- generates `s3_sector_report.md`\n- **does not claim block success when the compiled sector status is only `degraded_completed`**\n- emits `s3_failed.json` instead in that narrow-run case\n\n## What is now proven\n\n### Proven mechanically\n1. The real S3 operator agents exist in OpenClaw and are registered:\n   - `op_s3_human_subject_extractor`\n   - `op_s3_environment_location_extractor`\n   - `op_s3_object_artifact_extractor`\n   - `op_s3_symbolic_event_extractor`\n   - plus `sm_s3_visual_planning`\n\n2. A real operator invocation works end-to-end through OpenClaw:\n   - tested agent: `op_s3_human_subject_extractor`\n   - invocation path: `openclaw agent --agent op_s3_human_subject_extractor --message ...`\n   - the agent wrote:\n     - `output.json`\n     - `status.json`\n     - `checkpoint.json`\n\n3. The human operator output passed structural validation against the formal schema.\n\n4. The sector can be compiled from real operator output plus missing-operator gaps, producing:\n   - `compiled/compiled_entities.json`\n   - `compiled/s3_sector_report.md`\n\n5. The system can correctly distinguish:\n   - real operator success\n   - sector compile still being incomplete/degraded\n   - therefore block not actually ready for success closure\n\n### Proven artefact example\nNarrow real run:\n- `runtime_realcheck/run_004/`\n\nKey outputs:\n- `b2/sectors/s3_visual_planning/inputs/s3_source_package.json`\n- `b2/sectors/s3_visual_planning/checkpoints/operator_activation_plan.json`\n- `b2/sectors/s3_visual_planning/dispatch/human_subject_extractor_job.json`\n- `b2/sectors/s3_visual_planning/operators/human_subject_extractor/output.json`\n- `b2/sectors/s3_visual_planning/compiled/compiled_entities.json`\n- `b2/checkpoints/s3_failed.json`\n\n## What is still not proven\n\n1. **`b2_director` itself is not yet proven as a real invoked agent turn.**\n   The current validation used helpers to simulate the director’s mechanical responsibilities instead of invoking a real `b2_director` agent turn and observing it make the transition itself.\n\n2. **`sm_s3_visual_planning` itself is not yet proven as a real invoked supervisor turn.**\n   The current narrow run used helper scripts to prepare dispatch, then invoked one real operator directly.\n\n3. **The full S3 happy path with all required operators is not yet proven.**\n   The compile status for the narrow run is `degraded_completed`, not `completed`.\n\n4. **Resume semantics back into the director are not yet proven with a real agent turn.**\n   We have the checkpoints and helper logic, but not an observed real re-entry of `b2_director` on `s3_completed` / `s3_failed`.\n\n5. **Paperclip -> Perseus -> b2_director activation is not yet proven operationally.**\n   No live Paperclip-facing trigger was exercised here.\n\n## Current blocker statement for Perseus\nPaperclip should **not** yet assume that creating Perseus is enough to activate a coherent `b2_director -> S3` runtime.\n\nWhy:\n- the real operator layer is partially proven\n- the source-package + dispatch substrate is stronger now\n- but the actual control-plane agents (`b2_director`, `sm_s3_visual_planning`) are still not proven in a live turn-to-turn runtime loop\n- and the full-S3 success condition is still unproven\n\n## Recommended next validation tranche\n1. Invoke **real `sm_s3_visual_planning`** with the generated `s3.supervisor_bootstrap.v1` payload.\n2. Make the supervisor dispatch **only one allowed operator** in a controlled test mode, but own the dispatch itself.\n3. Observe the supervisor writing sector checkpoints itself.\n4. Then invoke **real `b2_director`** on bootstrap and on resume, instead of helper scripts.\n5. Only after those two control-plane agents are proven should Paperclip create Perseus to drive this path.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775233858677}}
{"type":"message","id":"2816c066","parentId":"6510483b","timestamp":"2026-04-03T16:31:15.199Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_02913ec245aa55fb0169cfeb4426dc8191afc3eb6bc7e251bf\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABpz-tFDTzXZU645CU3gAnQtCXHkfYz_cKKjwXS0sKIdJICqVlUa7AcACJMc8sNdODzcz7FI4DEyrZoMiPjq0TLYi7YzcFnFfJuFe0C1zOnZ0xJfNUDRS7I7Dh37QMHMqWmEuzea-Orxh7vIJtCZsB8ieVCx5uYTUUxWwl-kMQ4S2fKV78VuM8IH4TFFTo8tVaRqW4tKNsRHooPL_Tms9YQroJRaMIBR6GQZj7lsHx-J3Tykgojs2fBLuNnjznSUr0otgdWysj10zKIVc9xrcHjQtsDYIMpRSS0UoX0uyXqrlqDng3L7Lvyfll8fopVvXLbmnCSmc6WQ96psFOL9AfCYi76Xg19KDEX_nJMzY9W3OwviKm9wDxF2a3zzoGHVW8is-jLpwfyfiegcdVkL3h1p_G_HHlXaVkmqExt41Pdfu7uuApHvHD88tRL6vs7uQHmsAbXrh-sYpw8gpnItJB6XtVO1Rf8KgHyGT4wyg3prpMr__u8J-JxDTCE-xKg8qI0qPuK6l4KatfJuEf28BElUiaDpPY95r06UvwozXGbytHfBzYemXNdAlNPfKtGcCFhFNXgHsIcqCjN-qI5ZTeB30Kx26MSSAitaBvjFtbr_dX9_TPqJ7f3tj_2gaxaalqugZDXthW_EMnNRb9Wy0Wqurx49aint7YVru5HyKoPzXYCZ5UZ6Terzz8jMsL_6KaVa_8tWJiCZ4EXKa4n-8IM7fepaW56f466sb3gHM4DK9u9zYXR2b-9Kwm1lGJEabfbes5-v4Db6FgzYxFZ7OmXSAZo-4hPmAqCgEpWZAdSIERMJ1AUV7W1S0AUjKXxhJ_7BO5zFhWz6mKub5xhfp4JUywNkw==\",\"summary\":[]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_QqlCzlDour5ygA3QnUa1Jy9w|fc_02913ec245aa55fb0169cfeb450f3881919c0550e8de4bf4bb","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\content_factory_block2\\REAL_RUN_VALIDATION_2026-04-03.md","edits":[{"oldText":"## Recommended next validation tranche\n1. Invoke **real `sm_s3_visual_planning`** with the generated `s3.supervisor_bootstrap.v1` payload.\n2. Make the supervisor dispatch **only one allowed operator** in a controlled test mode, but own the dispatch itself.\n3. Observe the supervisor writing sector checkpoints itself.\n4. Then invoke **real `b2_director`** on bootstrap and on resume, instead of helper scripts.\n5. Only after those two control-plane agents are proven should Paperclip create Perseus to drive this path.\n","newText":"## Addendum — real control-plane probe executed after this note\n\n### Probe A — real `sm_s3_visual_planning` turn (`runtime_realcheck/run_005/`)\nWhat was observed:\n- the supervisor **was invoked for real** through `openclaw agent --agent sm_s3_visual_planning`\n- it successfully read the real bootstrap from disk\n- it wrote its own control-plane artefacts:\n  - `checkpoints/s3_supervisor_started.json`\n  - `checkpoints/operator_activation_plan.json`\n  - `dispatch/human_subject_extractor_job.json`\n  - `checkpoints/s3_final_checkpoint.json`\n- it also produced compiled sector artefacts under `compiled/`\n\nWhat was **not** observed:\n- the supervisor did **not** successfully launch a real subordinate operator under its own control\n- its own final checkpoint explicitly states:\n  - `status = degraded_completed`\n  - reason: `ACP runtime backend unavailable; real op_s3_human_subject_extractor session could not be launched.`\n\nInterpretation:\n- this proves a **partial real supervisor turn** (bootstrap ingestion + checkpoint/dispatch ownership)\n- this does **not** prove the decisive control-plane hop `supervisor -> real operator`\n- therefore the supervisor control-plane path is still **not fully proven**\n\n### Probe B — real `b2_director` invocation attempt (`runtime_realcheck/run_006/`)\nWhat was observed:\n- invoking `openclaw agent --agent b2_director ...` failed immediately\n- CLI error: `Unknown agent id \"b2_director\"`\n- `openclaw agents list` confirms that `b2_director` is **not registered** in the local OpenClaw agent registry, even though a folder exists at `.openclaw/agents/b2_director/`\n\nInterpretation:\n- the director is not just unproven — it is currently **not invokable as an OpenClaw agent** in this environment\n- bootstrap behavior and resume behavior therefore remain entirely unproven as live director turns\n\n## Recommended next validation tranche\n1. Fix the runtime registration gap for `b2_director` so it appears in `openclaw agents list`.\n2. Understand why nested real agent launches from `sm_s3_visual_planning` report `ACP runtime backend unavailable`, despite direct top-level operator invocations working from the shell.\n3. Re-run the supervisor probe and require one **actually launched** subordinate operator, not supervisor-authored fallback output.\n4. After `b2_director` is registered, run two real director turns:\n   - bootstrap on `b2.bootstrap.v1`\n   - resume on `b2.resume.v1` from an actual `s3_completed.json` or `s3_failed.json`\n5. Only after those two control-plane links are proven should Paperclip create Perseus to drive this path.\n"}]},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\content_factory_block2\\\\REAL_RUN_VALIDATION_2026-04-03.md\",\"edits\":[{\"oldText\":\"## Recommended next validation tranche\\n1. Invoke **real `sm_s3_visual_planning`** with the generated `s3.supervisor_bootstrap.v1` payload.\\n2. Make the supervisor dispatch **only one allowed operator** in a controlled test mode, but own the dispatch itself.\\n3. Observe the supervisor writing sector checkpoints itself.\\n4. Then invoke **real `b2_director`** on bootstrap and on resume, instead of helper scripts.\\n5. Only after those two control-plane agents are proven should Paperclip create Perseus to drive this path.\\n\",\"newText\":\"## Addendum — real control-plane probe executed after this note\\n\\n### Probe A — real `sm_s3_visual_planning` turn (`runtime_realcheck/run_005/`)\\nWhat was observed:\\n- the supervisor **was invoked for real** through `openclaw agent --agent sm_s3_visual_planning`\\n- it successfully read the real bootstrap from disk\\n- it wrote its own control-plane artefacts:\\n  - `checkpoints/s3_supervisor_started.json`\\n  - `checkpoints/operator_activation_plan.json`\\n  - `dispatch/human_subject_extractor_job.json`\\n  - `checkpoints/s3_final_checkpoint.json`\\n- it also produced compiled sector artefacts under `compiled/`\\n\\nWhat was **not** observed:\\n- the supervisor did **not** successfully launch a real subordinate operator under its own control\\n- its own final checkpoint explicitly states:\\n  - `status = degraded_completed`\\n  - reason: `ACP runtime backend unavailable; real op_s3_human_subject_extractor session could not be launched.`\\n\\nInterpretation:\\n- this proves a **partial real supervisor turn** (bootstrap ingestion + checkpoint/dispatch ownership)\\n- this does **not** prove the decisive control-plane hop `supervisor -> real operator`\\n- therefore the supervisor control-plane path is still **not fully proven**\\n\\n### Probe B — real `b2_director` invocation attempt (`runtime_realcheck/run_006/`)\\nWhat was observed:\\n- invoking `openclaw agent --agent b2_director ...` failed immediately\\n- CLI error: `Unknown agent id \\\"b2_director\\\"`\\n- `openclaw agents list` confirms that `b2_director` is **not registered** in the local OpenClaw agent registry, even though a folder exists at `.openclaw/agents/b2_director/`\\n\\nInterpretation:\\n- the director is not just unproven — it is currently **not invokable as an OpenClaw agent** in this environment\\n- bootstrap behavior and resume behavior therefore remain entirely unproven as live director turns\\n\\n## Recommended next validation tranche\\n1. Fix the runtime registration gap for `b2_director` so it appears in `openclaw agents list`.\\n2. Understand why nested real agent launches from `sm_s3_visual_planning` report `ACP runtime backend unavailable`, despite direct top-level operator invocations working from the shell.\\n3. Re-run the supervisor probe and require one **actually launched** subordinate operator, not supervisor-authored fallback output.\\n4. After `b2_director` is registered, run two real director turns:\\n   - bootstrap on `b2.bootstrap.v1`\\n   - resume on `b2.resume.v1` from an actual `s3_completed.json` or `s3_failed.json`\\n5. Only after those two control-plane links are proven should Paperclip create Perseus to drive this path.\\n\"}]}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":1403,"output":819,"cacheRead":44928,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":47150,"cost":{"input":0.0035075,"output":0.012285,"cacheRead":0.011231999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0270245}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775233858686,"responseId":"resp_02913ec245aa55fb0169cfeb42f95881918750968086f1c76f"}}
